  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user I want to clearly understand which message is read and which isn't for system messages. \r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\nWe have to fix how systems messages are shown now in a chat list view.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n1. Seen system messages should have a grey color as a normal chat seen messages\r\n2. System messages regarding geo position should be shown in one line as other messages. \r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n1. Seen system messages look like as unseen new messages because they have a black color.\r\n2. System message regarding geo position is shown in 2 lines and brake layout.\r\n\r\n![slice](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6559881/33370162-0b287984-d4f7-11e7-87c4-72d3851134e7.png)\r\n\r\n",
